    description: 'Researchers demonstrate "shelving" populations into the |2⟩ or |3⟩ state right before measurement. <strong>Contribution:</strong> Because T1 relaxation strictly happens from |n⟩ to |n-1⟩, shelving a logical |1⟩ into |2⟩ protects the state from decaying to |0⟩ during the slow readout envelope, dramatically lowering measurement error.'
